Here's the deal. I'm still waiting to hear back from Gem since our last encounter. She may or may not be serious about walking away. If she is serious, we could try to find another buyer but it would be hard to pin-point someone that would pay top dollar for a start-up business.


IF Gem comes back with more hostility, we need to drop the offer. You're going to be better off getting all you can out of Pickle b/c any other company likely won't pay as much as she will. Plus, you get the added bonus of taking money from her - every dollar out of her pocket is twice as sweet as a dollar from someone else.


If they don't budge, we need to come down to $50k (plus half the money in the bank) and we need to be ready to settle for $45-46k if they counter. I know this seems lower than what we were after, but it may be the best we can do. On the bright side, that would pay for most of lawschool if you really did want to go back.


Let me know what you think. I'll be back in touch when Gem e-mails me again.

